org.openimaj.image.processor

Interface KernelProcessor<Q,I extends Image<Q,I>>

  • Type Parameters:
    Q - The pixel type that is processed
    I - The image type that is processed
    All Superinterfaces:
    Processor<I>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SinglebandKernelProcessor<T,I>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Dilate, Erode, FSobelMagnitude, HitAndMiss

    public interface KernelProcessor<Q,I extends Image<Q,I>>
extends Processor<I>
    A kernel processor interface for objects that are able to process an image using convolution. Patches are generated for every pixel in the image where a patch of the size required by this class can be placed. The processKernel(Image) function will then generate a single value which is used to build the convolved image.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
